d: The fourth letter of the English alphabet and a vocal consonent The English letter is from Latin which is from Greek which took it from Phoenician the probable ultimate origin being Egyptian It is related most nearly to t and th as Eng deep G tief Eng daughter G tochter Gr duhitr See Guide to Pronunciation sq root178 179 22
Mus The nominal of the second tone in the model major scale that in C or of the fourth tone in the relative minor scale of C that in A minor or of the key tone in the relative minor of F
As a numeral D stands for 50
in this use it is not the initial of any word or even strictly a letter but one half of the sign
